-- Polymetal, Razgulay, Rosneft: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2010-10-01T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/polymetal-razgulay-rosneft-russian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock Micex Index added 1.5 percent to 1,440.30 at
the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 0.9
percent to 1,507.66.  OAO Polyus Gold  (PLZL RX): Gold futures fell from a record,
with December futures falling 0.8 percent to $1,299.30 an ounce,
as the dollar halted a slide, eroding demand for the precious
metal as an alternative investment. Russia’s biggest gold
producer added 1.7 percent to 1,412.65 rubles.  OAO Polymetal 
(PMTL RX), a gold and silver producer, rose 1.6 percent to
464.21 rubles.  OAO Razgulay  (GRAZ RX): The potential for Russia’s wheat
crop in 2011 is worse than traders may think because late
planting has shortened the growing season before the onset of
winter, according to agricultural forecaster Martell Crop
Projections. The Russian grain and sugar producer added 0.1
percent to 44.409 rubles.  OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Crude oil rose, adding 1.9 percent
to $79.32 a barrel and heading for the biggest monthly gain
since May 2009. Russia’s biggest oil company added 1.6 percent
to 203.71 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Denis Maternovsky  in Moscow at 
 dmaternovsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
